<paragraph blockId="8.[178,1085,1433,1572]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1261">
C o m m e n t: The distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2004" box="[558,669,1433,1455]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Medon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="1261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lydicus">
<emphasis box="[558,669,1433,1455]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="1261">M. lydicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ranges from western 
<collectingCountry box="[907,994,1433,1455]" name="Turkey" pageId="8" pageNumber="1261">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
and the Greek islands Rhodos, Samos, Ikaria, and Lesbos across 
<collectingCountry box="[757,844,1462,1484]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="8" pageNumber="1261">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
to southeastern 
<collectingCountry name="Serbia" pageId="8" pageNumber="1261">Yugoslavia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[241,390,1491,1513]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1261" pagination="33 - 82" refId="ref12080" refString="ASSING V. (2004 a): A revision of the Medon species of the Eastern Mediterranean and adjacent regions (Insecta: Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Bonner zoologische Beitrage 52: 33 - 82." type="journal article" year="2004">ASSING 2004a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[401,465,1491,1513]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1261" pagination="1027 - 1034" refId="ref12160" refString="ASSING V. (2005 a): A revision of Western Palaearctic Medon. IV. A new species and new records from Iran, and a catalogue of species (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae, Paederinae). - Linzer biologische Beitrage 37 (2): 1027 - 1034." type="journal article" year="2005">2005a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[476,542,1491,1513]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1261" pagination="1035 - 1046" refId="ref12212" refString="ASSING V. (2005 b): Two new species and new records of Staphylinidae from the Greek island Lesbos (Insecta: Coleoptera). - Linzer biologische Beitrage 37 (2): 1035 - 1046." type="journal article" year="2005">2005b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[552,620,1491,1513]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1261" pagination="23 - 32" refId="ref12345" refString="ASSING V. (2007 b): A revision of Western Palaearctic Medon. V. A new species from Iran and additional records (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae, Paederinae). - Linzer biologische Beitrage 39 (1): 23 - 32." type="journal article" year="2007">2007b</bibRefCitation>
). The specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[843,908,1491,1513]" name="Serbia" pageId="8" pageNumber="1261">Serbia</collectingCountry>
represents a new country record and considerably expands the known distribution of the species northwestwards (
<figureCitation box="[297,367,1550,1572]" captionStart="Map 2" captionStartId="9.[178,223,1058,1078]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,465,1034]" captionTargetId="figure-87@9.[178,1085,465,1034]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Map 2: Distributions of Medon lydicus BORDONI (filled circles) and M. subfusculus FAGEL (open circles) based on revised records." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5276597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5276597/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="1261">Map 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
